<title>FRANCE: EU set to approve GAN restructuring - paper.</title>
<headline>EU set to approve GAN restructuring - paper.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1996-09-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>The European Commission is to give the green light on Wednesday to the 1995 restructuring plan of French state-controlled insurer GAN, the business daily Les Echos reported on Tuesday.</p>
<p>The restructuring included a 2.8 billion franc recapitalisation of the insurer aimed at paving the way for its privatisation as well as a multi-billion franc asset disposal programme.</p>
<p>The Commission had said it wanted to examine whether the recapitalisation constituted state aid and had complained it received insufficient notification from the French government of the move.</p>
<p>But the insurer, which is selling a majority stake of its holding in regional banking group CIC as part of the restructuring, had always said it was confident that it would receive the Commission's approval.</p>
